Port uu_install 0.8.0 to a NATIVE in-process brush builtin, like uu_cp/uu_mkdir.
Two divergences, both local to vendor/uu_install:

* Logical I/O: a new entry install_main(args, cwd, out, err) runs on the
  builtin's worker thread writing the shell's logical sinks, never the process's
  fd 1/2. The verbose writeln!(stdout(), …) sites target an InstallOut buffer
  sink; uucore show!/show_error!/show_if_err! are shadowed to INSTALL_ERR; the
  set_exit_code sites are shadowed to defer onto a thread-local INSTALL_EXIT. The
  child mode module (declared before the crate-local macros) routes its one
  diagnostic through a pub(crate) buffer_error helper. The entry drains the
  buffers and surfaces the status.
* Logical cwd: brush never chdir's the process, so the shared run(args, cwd) body
  resolves every relative path operand and the -t/--target-directory value
  against the shell's logical cwd.

The standalone #[uucore::main] uumain bridge is retained (drains to real stdio).

